A group of teachers walking together in a township near their school can never hide. They are recognised instinctively. How they are pointed out requires some research but we do not know nor can we hazard a guess as to why they stand out.
There were times when they would be seen with jerry cans during payday; they would line up at a bank and after that they would buy paraffin, meat and other supplies before getting into a bar to refresh themselves with cold beer. It was a custom and everybody knew teachers have been paid. In fact, the payday was some sort of a day off from school. It really was a waste.



