That trend went out of vogue and new pay methods have come up and made the teachers somewhat invisible but still recognisable. These days, it is customary to see unhappy teachers in a group in town seeking a cybercafé where they would crowd together. This happens thrice every year and we just found out that their employer demands that they fill in Tpad every term.
Some may ask what Tpad is: Well, it is the acronym for Teacher Performance Appraisal and Development. The thing speaks for itself and it is a harmless document that seeks to quantify things that can never be quantified. It takes teachers from the rural depths so much time to fumble and fill out and submit the Tpad online to their employer.



